%description:
Regression test for D8 (workstream D, architecture decoupling): ~RsvpTe::handleStopOperation
now sends a forced PathTear downstream for every session THIS node originated (i.e. every
path in its own `traffic` list) BEFORE clearing its local state, instead of silently
`clear()`-ing and leaving downstream peers to notice the dead adjacency and time their own
state out on their own (RFC 2205 Section 3.7's (K + 0.5) * 1.5 * R state-lifetime formula,
which with this network's default refreshInterval=30s/stateLifetimeFactor=3 is 157.5s --
vastly longer than the propagation delay this test actually observes below).
~RsvpTe::handleCrashOperation is intentionally left untouched (still silent `clear()`-only):
a crash is definitionally not a graceful event, so no PathTear should be sent for one.

Built on the shipped examples/mpls/testte_reroute network (RSVPTE4) and its default traffic
configuration (LSR1_rsvp.xml): LSR1 is the ingress for two permanent sessions -- tunnel_id 1
to host3 (route LSR1->LSR3->LSR7->LSR5) and tunnel_id 2 to host4 (route
LSR1->LSR2->LSR4->LSR5) -- so LSR1 is exactly the kind of "session-originating" node D8
targets. This test replaces testte_reroute's own scenario.xml (which reroutes/tears down via
scripted <add-session>/<del-session> commands, already covered by rsvpte_setup_tear.test)
with a single <shutdown module="LSR1"/> at t=2s, to exercise handleStopOperation's new code
path specifically.

Note on this workstream's other examples: testte_failure/testte_failure2/net37 all *do*
shut down an RsvpTe-capable router (LSR4) in their shipped scenarios, but LSR4 is always a
transit hop there (only LSR1/LSR2 carry `rsvp.traffic`, i.e. are session-ingresses) -- so
their `traffic` list is empty and this new code path is a no-op for them; this is why their
fingerprint rows are unaffected by this commit despite superficially "stopping an RSVP
router". This test is the one that actually exercises an INGRESS shutting down.

Asserted, in order:
  1. the shutdown fires;
  2. one of LSR1's two downstream neighbors (LSR2 or LSR3, whichever the log shows first)
     receives and processes the resulting PathTear (RsvpTe::processPathTearMsg's "Received
     PATH_TEAR" log line);
  3. that neighbor removes its own path (and, if already reserved, reservation) state
     (RsvpTe::removePSB's "removing PSB ..." log line, straight from the shared teardown
     path processPathTearMsg/delSession already use);
  4. the PathTear arrives well within 100ms of the t=2s shutdown -- i.e. promptly, not via
     the ~157.5s RFC 2205 timeout that would otherwise be the only mechanism;
  5. standard undisposed-object postrun guard (clean teardown, no crash).

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: scenario.xml
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<scenario>
    <at t="2s">
        <shutdown module="LSR1"/>
    </at>
</scenario>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.testte_reroute.RSVPTE4
sim-time-limit = 3s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "info"

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host4.rt"
**.host5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/host5.rt"

**.LSR1.classifier.config = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR1_fec.xml")
**.LSR1.rsvp.traffic = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR1_rsvp.xml")

**.LSR*.rsvp.helloInterval = 0.2s
**.LSR*.rsvp.helloTimeout = 0.5s

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR5.rt"
**.LSR6.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR6.rt"
**.LSR7.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_reroute/LSR7.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

*.*.hasStatus = true
# D8: a plain node shutdown of the ingress (LSR1), no scripted add-session/del-session
**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 1-3. ordered: the shutdown fires -> a downstream neighbor receives the resulting
%# PathTear -> it removes its own path state (and reservation state, if already made)
%contains-regex: stdout
processing <shutdown> command\.\.\.
.*
Received PATH_TEAR
.*
removing PSB
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 4. the PathTear arrives well within 100ms of the t=2s shutdown (propagation delay
%# only) -- vastly promptly compared to the ~157.5s RFC 2205 refresh/timeout interval
%# this network would otherwise fall back on (refreshInterval=30s default,
%# stateLifetimeFactor=3: (3 + 0.5) * 1.5 * 30s = 157.5s)
%postrun-command: awk '/^\*\* Event #/ { if (match($0, /t=([0-9.]+)/, m)) t = m[1]+0 } /Received PATH_TEAR/ && t >= 2 && t < 2.1 { print "PROMPT_PATH_TEAR", t }' test.out > prompt_path_tear.out
%contains: prompt_path_tear.out
PROMPT_PATH_TEAR
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
